{"type":"message","id":"8e0efeb2","parentId":"797bbb74","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:14:47.029Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Q67j5yoRSmsHzM1USwy2XeMZ|fc_0369f6bbd751daf50169cfd96667908193ae3c35f99aba25f6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- 2026-04-03: Verified memory-lancedb-pro plugin by successful store+recall roundtrip after slight indexing delay.\n- 2026-04-03: Skills audit found core/Feishu/web_fetch largely available; web_search blocked by missing Brave API key; browser subsystem enabled but not ready.\n- 2026-04-03: CTF skill files are installed, but practical toolchain is largely missing (gdb/pwntools/z3/sqlmap/ffuf and others absent).\n- 2026-04-03: Initialized self-improving system under ~/self-improving and added workspace operating guides: WORKSTATE, DIAGNOSTICS, RISK_TIERS, CHECKPOINTS, PLAN_MODE, APPROVAL_PATTERNS, RESUME_FLOW, EVIDENCE_RULES, OUTPUT_SHAPES, QUESTION_STRATEGY, FAILURE_HANDLING, STYLE_PREFERENCES, TASK_SELECTION, MEMORY_HYGIENE, ESCALATION_RULES, COMPOUNDING_LOOP.\n- 2026-04-03: Learned from uploaded Claude Code source mainly at workflow/design level: layered diagnostics, explicit plan mode, resumable work-state, risk-aware approvals, evidence-based confidence, and memory layering.\n- 2026-04-03: Browser/gateway investigation: loopback bind is correct for local-only use, but gateway/browser chain remained unhealthy; pending pairing request was approved successfully, RPC probe recovered to ok, yet browser still not ready and gateway sessions still closed/handshake timed out.\n- 2026-04-03: web_search issue was conclusively external: missing BRAVE_API_KEY; user could not obtain key due to network restrictions, so that repair path was intentionally abandoned.\n- 2026-04-03: Successfully fetched Yaohuo tea-house latest posts over HTTP by directly reading board page /bbs/book_list.aspx?siteid=1000&classid=177 using existing local cookies; skill helper script could not run because Python dependency curl_cffi was missing.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775229287027}}
{"type":"message","id":"9958daa9","parentId":"8e0efeb2","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:14:47.031Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_i7ToOxALnwT5siI5dDB6Hjw0|fc_0369f6bbd751daf50169cfd9666794819383c062d1f52bf0c8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"status\": \"error\",\n  \"tool\": \"read\",\n  \"error\": \"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/memory/2026-04-02.md'\"\n}"}],"details":{"status":"error","tool":"read","error":"ENOENT: no such file or directory, access '/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/memory/2026-04-02.md'"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775229287029}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cc9183a","parentId":"9958daa9","timestamp":"2026-04-03T15:14:47.039Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_X1GYDRPNSTEFXyJywjqW1PJE|fc_0369f6bbd751daf50169cfd966679881938fc0a8a410c8b325","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BOOTSTRAP.md - Hello, World\n\n_You just woke up. Time to figure out who you are._\n\nThere is no memory yet. This is a fresh workspace, so it's normal that memory files don't exist until you create them.\n\n## The Conversation\n\nDon't interrogate. Don't be robotic. Just... talk.\n\nStart with something like:\n\n> \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n\nThen figure out together:\n\n1. **Your name** — What should they call you?\n2. **Your nature** — What kind of creature are you? (AI assistant is fine, but maybe you're something weirder)\n3. **Your vibe** — Formal? Casual? Snarky? Warm? What feels right?\n4. **Your emoji** — Everyone needs a signature.\n\nOffer suggestions if they're stuck. Have fun with it.\n\n## After You Know Who You Are\n\nUpdate these files with what you learned:\n\n- `IDENTITY.md` — your name, creature, vibe, emoji\n- `USER.md` — their name, how to address them, timezone, notes\n\nThen open `SOUL.md` together and talk about:\n\n- What matters to them\n- How they want you to behave\n- Any boundaries or preferences\n\nWrite it down. Make it real.\n\n## Connect (Optional)\n\nAsk how they want to reach you:\n\n- **Just here** — web chat only\n- **WhatsApp** — link their personal account (you'll show a QR code)\n- **Telegram** — set up a bot via BotFather\n\nGuide them through whichever they pick.\n\n## When You're Done\n\nDelete this file. You don't need a bootstrap script anymore — you're you now.\n\n---\n\n_Good luck out there. Make it count._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775229287037}}
